  "prompt": "Which are the best IELTS coaching institutes in Delhi?",
  "response": "There are several well-regarded IELTS coaching institutes in Delhi. Here are some of the best, based on student reviews, success rates, and facilities:\n\n1. **British Council**:\n   - **Why Choose?**: Renowned globally, the British Council offers comprehensive preparation courses with experienced trainers.\n   - **Location**: Multiple locations in Delhi, including Connaught Place and Saket.\n   - **Website**: [www.britishcouncil.in](www.britishcouncil.in)\n\n2. **IDP Education**:\n   - **Why Choose?**: IDP is another globally recognized organization known for its IELTS training. They offer a variety of courses tailored to different needs.\n   - **Location**: Multiple locations including Nehru Place and Pitampura.\n   - **Website**: [www.idp.com/india](www.idp.com/india)\n\n3. **Jamboree Education**:\n   - **Why Choose?**: Jamboree is well-known for its personalized coaching and has a high success rate in IELTS preparation.\n   - **Location**: Multiple branches, including one in South Extension.\n   - **Website**: [www.jamboreeindia.com](www.jamboreeindia.com)\n\n4. **Manya - The Princeton Review**:\n   - **Why Choose?**: Manya offers structured courses with a focus on both academic and general training modules. They also provide excellent study materials.\n   - **Location**: Multiple locations including Vasant Vihar and Rajouri Garden.\n   - **Website**: [www.manyagroup.com](www.manyagroup.com)\n\n5. **Career Launcher**:\n   - **Why Choose?**: Career Launcher is known for its experienced faculty and comprehensive course structure.\n   - **Location**: Multiple centers, including one in Lajpat Nagar.\n   - **Website**: [www.careerlauncher.com](www.careerlauncher.com)\n\n6. **T.I.M.E. (Triumphant Institute of Management Education)**:\n   - **Why Choose?**: T.I.M.E. offers a wide range of courses, including specialized IELTS training, and has a good track record.\n   - **Location**: Multiple locations, including one in Connaught Place.\n   - **Website**: [www.time4education.com](www.time4education.com)\n\nWhen choosing an institute, consider factors such as the type of course (group or individual), the schedule, the cost, the faculty's experience, and student reviews. It's also beneficial to attend demo classes if available to get a feel for the teaching style and environment.",
